  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "NPM respects the `repository` field, and it allows us to specify subdirectory, i.e. for monorepo purposes!\r\n\r\nAll packages in this monorepo should probably have this populated, e.g.:\r\n```javascript\r\n{\r\n  \"name\": \"@truffle/core\",\r\n  /* ... */\r\n  \"repository\": {\r\n    \"type\": \"git\",\r\n    \"url\": \"https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle.git\",\r\n    \"directory\": \"packages/core\"\r\n  },\r\n  /* ... */\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n(Raised by @haltman-at [here](https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/pull/3943#discussion_r617047761))",
